The sales staff is pretty good too, not that i have any time at all to talk to any of them though cause we are the busiest lab pretty much in the entire NW region. I LOVE IT!! Lab work is so fun. So i say now....wait till xmas season is over and i may not be saying that, but i dont have to talk to customers!! YEAHYEAHYEAH!!!

IM HAPPY!!!   Work is going good so far, school is almost over...im actually skipping right now, it  was either walk in late or  skip altogether. i chose door C!!!  

I feel bad i havent been home all weekend long. But cori and kitties you must forgive me, i dont get to see Cade again untill next weekend cause he has to work about 60-70 hours or so this week, plus he has band practice and the likes when hes not working or sleeping.  
Saturday i skipped out on Vertigo, brandons going to kill me cause i skipped friday to work on albums all night.  Cade and i went to dinner at Eagle Tai...so great. Then we went to see The Matrix at Century 16 on 82nd.  They were sold out so we wandered till the next one.  (I shall not comment on the movie)  After that we went home to his place and went to sleep. (SLEEP)  We both had work early in the morning and played phone tag all day, then hung out again after i got off of owrk. Played a few games of pool at the Bonfire, got a frozen pizza for dinner, hung out with some of his friends for a bit. then went to bed and slept (Slept)  Some how his alarm didnt go off this morning. He was supposed to be to work at 7.30am, i looked at the clock at 7.42am!! SUCK!!  Work again today, but its a mid shift so i will be home by 7.30pm which is so great. 
A few possibilities for the evening...
brandon fixing my star tattoos (prolly not though since i didnt show up saturday)
watching movies and working on a wedding album (must finish by tomorrow)

yeah no owrk or school tomorrow, that means laundry day!! MMMMM  and maybe possibly TOP BURGER for lunch!! NUM!!!   right. so off to get ready for work.
